Boil a full #kettle{}.

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%grams}(halved lengthways), then cut into thirds widthways.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once boiled, pour the water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @rigatoni pasta{180%grams} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the @diced chorizo{90%grams} and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and garlic. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%grams}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%grams}, @sugar{1%tsp}(for the sauce) and @water{100%milliliters}(for the sauce).

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

When the rigatoni has been cooking for about 8 mins, add the Tenderstem® to the same pan and bring back to the boil.

Cook with the pasta for the last ~{4%minutes} of cooking time.

Once cooked, drain the pasta and broccoli in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the tomato sauce has thickened, add the @butter{20%grams} and @baby spinach{40%grams} to the pan, a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir the cooked pasta, broccoli, @peas{120%grams} and three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%grams} into the sauce. Heat through until the peas are piping hot, ~{1%minute} more.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash more water if you feel it needs it.

Share the pasta out between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the remaining cheese to finish. Enjoy!